The historic Sling 4 aircraft which flew from Cape Town to Cairo is back on South African soil. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The historic Sling four aircraft which flew from Cape Town to Cairo is back on South African soil. The young men and women who built the plane are all teenagers who created the opportunity to fly in their own aeroplane. From Cape to Cairo: SA teens fly plane across Africa Twenty teenagers built the four-seater sling plane and six young pilots flew it from Cape to Cairo and back. The teens all plan to continue flying, and hopefully commercially, soon. Watch the full report in the video above The historic Sling 4 aircraft which flew from Cape Town to Cairo is back on South African soil.